Our aim is to bring you up to speed with all the current projects in development whether they are being funded through the <a href="https://travel.portsmouth.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Local-Transport-Plan-2021.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://pompeybug.us5.list-manage.com/track/click?u%3D2ed916007f1c294faa614a50f%26id%3D5434e8e863%26e%3D1021f7a16d&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1674423054885000&amp;usg=AOvVaw3UIRfNC1gFom-WcbcNXRKq">Local Transport Plan</a>, <a href="https://www.sehrt.org.uk/schemes/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://pompeybug.us5.list-manage.com/track/click?u%3D2ed916007f1c294faa614a50f%26id%3D3dead60499%26e%3D1021f7a16d&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1674423054885000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1x0Kk4AvINJC4IsrFxEdXR">South East Hants Rapid Transit projects</a> or are being developed through the wider regeneration of the city.  We hope to have time for some questions, but some of us will probably retire to a local hostelry to discuss the issues raised, if you want to continue the conversation.

We aim to start promptly at 7pm on Thursday 26th January and will finish at 8:45pm. We are returning to the University's Richmond Building. Full details and to register in advance can be found via this <strong><a href="https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/open-public-meeting-tickets-462527852257">link</a></strong>

